Charles F. Marcy  Founder, President, and Chief Executive Officer, Healthy Food Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Mr. Charles F. Marcy, also known as Chuck, has been the Chief Executive Officer at Turtle MountainÂ LLC since May 2013. Mr. Marcy serves as a Principal at MarcyÂ & Partners,Â Inc., and provides strategic planning and acquisition consulting to companies with a consumer focus. He Founded Healthy Food Holdings, LLC and served as its Chief Executive Officer and President from 2005 to April 2010. He served as Chief Executive Officer, President and Director at Horizon Organic ... Holding Corp. from January 2000 to February 23, 2007. He joined Horizon Organic Holding Corp., as Chief Operating Officer in November 1999. Before joining the firm, Mr. Marcy served as President and Chief Executive Officer at the Sealright Corporation. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer at Huhtamaki Consumer Packaging, Inc. from August 1995 to 1998. He served as President of Horizon Organic since November 1999. From 1993 to 1998, he served as President of the Golden Grain Company from April 1993 to August 1995. From 1991 to 1993, Mr. Marcy served as President of National Dairy Products Corp. He served as an Executive Director of Horizon Organic Holding Corp., since November 1999. From 1974 to 1991, Mr. Marcy served various senior marketing and strategic planning roles at Sara Lee Corporation and Kraft General Foods, both food manufacturing and marketing companies. He has been an Independent Director of Farmer Brothers Co. since December 5, 2013. Mr. Marcy serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Avrio Capital Management Corporation. Mr. Marcy has been a Director of Huhtamaki Consumer Packaging, Inc. since 1995 and Outside Director of B&G Foods Inc. since October 19, 2010. He serves as a Director of the International Dairy Foods Association, the Organic Trade Association and Community Food Share. He was a Member of Advisory Board at Avrio Capital Inc. Mr. Marcy served as a Member of the Board of Directors at Healthy Food Holdings Inc. from 2005 to April 2010. He has an Undergraduate Degree in Mathematics and Economics from Washington and Jefferson College and a Masters of Business Administration Degree, with a concentration in Marketing and General Management, from the Harvard Business School.Read Full Background




